name: The Impassable Speed Labyrinth
description:
A difficult, top-down, reaction-time based game where you have to reach the end of the level without touching the hedge(which will eat you) and escape the labyrinth

Simple really, except there's more to the labyrinth than that, given the whole 'the walls will eat me' thing AND the fact that it's called 'The Impassable Speed Labyrinth', impassable literally means 'impossible to travel along' and what's with the 'speed' thing, you'd guess that someone named it that for a reason and you'd be right

So then, will you escape The Impassable Speed Labyrinth? or will it instead break your will as you succumb to madness?

"Only one with many keyboards might truly escape the labyrinth"
-Labyrinth Guardian "'Keyboards'?"
-Onlooker

Impassable speed labyrinth fun facts

  • There are 35 levels in total
  • The first 7 levels length is exactly 420m
  • The first 10 levels length is 699m
  • The labyrinth is exactly 11.454Km long

-Society for Impassable Labyrinths
